# Greenfield Township, Warren County, Iowa

Greenfield Township is one of the sixteen townships of Warren County, Iowa, United States. Its estimated population as of 2008 is 5,773 people, with a density of . Three cities have land in Greenfield (Norwalk, Spring Hill, and Des Moinesâ€”the state capital), as well as two unincorporated areas (Greenbush and Scotch Ridge). The township has two cemeteries (Webb Cemetery and North Ridge).
Geography
At an elevation of , Greenfield Township covers an area of . The North River, a tributary of the Des Moines River, passes through Greenfield Township.
